Create IAM users and groups with limited access â€” specifically, users who can access only S3, and test their permissions using AWS CLI.

1. Install AWS CLI
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/getting-started-install.html
msiexec.exe /i https://awscli.amazonaws.com/AWSCLIV2.msi

2. Create IAM Groups

3. Create IAM Users

4. Configure AWS CLI with the User just created
aws configure --profile s3user


AWS Access Key ID     [Your Key ID]
AWS Secret Access Key [Your Secret Key]
Default region name    us-east-2
Default output format  json


5. Restricting other users
aws ec2 describe-instances --profile s3user

